HEADWORD: Haulabout
<hw>Haul"a*bout`</hw> <pr>(h⟦add⟧l"⟦adot⟧*bout`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A bargelike vessel with steel hull, large hatchways, and coal
transporters, for coaling war vessels from its own hold or from other
colliers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

